    <summaries>
      <summary>
        <versionCode>00</versionCode>
        <actionDate>2007-03-28</actionDate>
        <actionDesc>Introduced in House</actionDesc>
        <updateDate>2007-05-10T22:18:32Z</updateDate>
        <text><![CDATA[ <p>Veterans' Care Advocate Act - Directs the Secretary of Defense to establish within each Department of Defense (DOD) military medical treatment facility an Ombudsman for Recovering Servicemembers to act as a liaison for recovering servicemembers and their families with respect to their evaluation and care under the physical disability evaluation systems.</p> <p>Defines as &quot;recovering servicemembers&quot; those in a medical hold or holdover status due to an injury, illness, or disease incurred or aggravated while on active duty.</p>]]></text>
      </summary>
    </summaries>
    <title>Veterans' Care Advocate Act</title>
    <titles>
      <item>
        <titleType>Official Title as Introduced</titleType>
        <title>To establish an Ombudsman in the Department of Defense to assist members of the Armed Forces seeking medical care at military medical treatment facilities.</title>
        <billTextVersionName>Introduced in House</billTextVersionName>
        <billTextVersionCode>IH</billTextVersionCode>
